SIMPLE: salient
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Salient
<hw>Sa"li*ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>saliens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>salire</ets> to
leap; cf. F. <ets>saillant</ets>. See <er>Sally</er>, <pos>n.</pos> &
<pos>v. i.</pos>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Moving by leaps or springs;
leaping; bounding; jumping.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Frogs and <xex>salient</xex>
animals.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Shooting out or up; springing; projecting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He had in himself a <qex>salient</qex>, living spring of generous
and manly action.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Hence, figuratively, forcing itself on the
attention; prominent; conspicuous; noticeable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He [Grenville] had neither <qex>salient</qex> traits, nor general
comprehensiveness of mind.</q> <rj><qau>Bancroft.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Math. & Fort.)</fld> <def>Projecting outwardly;
<as>as, a <ex>salient</ex> angle</as>; -- opposed to
<contr>reentering</contr>.</def><-- convex? -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Represented in a leaping position;
<as>as, a lion <ex>salient</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Salient angle</b></col>. <cd>See <er>Salient</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>, 4.</cd> -- <col><b>Salient polygon</b></col>
<fld>(Geom.)</fld>, <cd>a polygon all of whose angles are salient.</cd>
-- <col><b>Salient polyhedron</b></col> <fld>(Geom.)</fld>, <cd>a
polyhedron all of whose solid angles are salient.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Salient</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Salient
<hw>Sa"li*ent</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Fort.)</fld> <def>A salient
angle or part; a projection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saliently</ent>⟦br⟧
